~How to Compile~
1. Run Makefile through terminal.
2. Execute the executable with name PlyRenderer with name of any ply file as run time argument.
Ex. : ./PlyRenderer bunny.ply 
	./PlyRenderer dragon.ply


~Expected Inputs~
Mouse:
1. Click and drag left button of mouse to rotate object.
2. Use right button of mouse to bring popup menu.
3. Use shift+left mouse button (drag up-down) to change distance of camera from object.
4. Use middle mouse button(drag) to translate object.

Keyboard Shortcuts:
5. Use +/- of keyboard for zooming the object at once.
6. b : switch background color between black/white.
7. p : To switch between point cloud and filled version of object.
8. w : To switch between wireframe and filled version of object.
9. n : To switch between per-fragment and per-vertex normals.
10. l : Rotate light with object(Select colored left-light first to see clearly, using popup menu). Only left light will move with object, right light will remain steady. 

~Notable Defects~
none.


